[1]
Date: Sun 10 Apr 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Australian Broadcasting Corporation, Agence France Presse report,
Sun 10 Apr 2005 [edited]
<http://www.abc.net.au/news/newsitems/200504/s1342006.htm>

Cambodia: 3rd avian influenza death confirmed
-----------------------------------------------
Cambodia has confirmed its 3rd fatality from avian influenza, with an
8-year-old girl becoming the latest victim to die in the kingdom.
"According to our initial investigations, the girl died from avian
influenza. We have received confirmation from the Pasteur Institute in
Phnom Penh," the Head of the Health Ministry's infectious disease
department, Ly Sovann, told Agence France Presse (AFP).
Ly Sovann said the girl was from the southern province of Kampot bordering
Viet Nam, where 36 deaths have been reported since the end of 2003. 12
people have also died in Thailand from H5N1 virus infection.
The girl died on Thursday [7 Apr 2005] night at Phnom Penh's
privately-funded Kantha Bopha hospital, he said, adding that samples had
been sent abroad for further confirmation that she died of H5N1 virus
infection. He was not immediately able to provide further details.
Cambodia's other 2 victims were also from Kampot province. The 3rd reported
fatality was a 25-year-old woman who died in Viet Nam in January [2005]
after seeking treatment there. The 2nd victim was a 28-year-old man from
the same province who died in March [2005].
--
